2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses an L1-cost function and Iterative Re-weighted Least Squares, which are common techniques in machine learning.
3. cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible category as camera matrices are also used in computer graphics for rendering and image synthesis.
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category as camera matrices are used in robotics for tasks such as visual odometry and SLAM.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as camera matrices are used in multimedia applications such as video stabilization and object tracking.
